</p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><font style="font-size:1.2em">A 74-room mansion used by Napoleon Bonaparte as his headquarters during a famous battle has been put up for sale.</font></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><font style="font-size:1.2em">Villa La Voglina in Piedmont, Italy, was built in the 18th century by the world-renowned Baroque architect Filippo Juvarra.</font></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><font style="font-size:1.2em">The historic property is set in 60 acres and boasts 13 bedrooms, nine bathrooms and a private chapel with seating for 30 people.</font></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><font style="font-size:1.2em">It is on the market at £3.8million with Beauchamp Estates, which also has a two-bedroom flat for sale at a similar price in London’s Belgravia.</font></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><font style="font-size:1.2em"><span class="mol-style-bold">Scroll down for video  </span></font></p><div class="mol-img-group xwArtSplitter">    <div class="mol-img">  <img id="i-cee314df3bab0f4f" src="http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2015/02/08/2574FC4000000578-0-image-a-27_1423405620701.jpg" height="845" width="962" alt="Beautiful property: Villa La Voglina in Piedmont, Italy, was built in the 18th Century by the world renowned Baroque architect Filippo Juvarra" class="blkBorder img-share"/>
</div>    <p class="imageCaption">Beautiful property: Villa La Voglina in Piedmont, Italy, was built in the 18th Century by the world renowned Baroque architect Filippo Juvarra</p></div><div class="mol-img-group xwArtSplitter">    <div class="mol-img">  <img id="i-c0b250f5e7986c26" src="http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2015/02/08/2574FCA800000578-0-image-a-28_1423405627528.jpg" height="641" width="962" alt="Stunning interior: The property is set in 60 acres and boasts 13 bedrooms, nine bathrooms and a private chapel with seating for 30 people" class="blkBorder img-share"/>
</div>    <p class="imageCaption">Stunning interior: The property is set in 60 acres and boasts 13 bedrooms, nine bathrooms and a private chapel with seating for 30 people</p></div><div class="mol-img-group xwArtSplitter">    <div class="mol-img">  <img id="i-e0473222acaab6d1" src="http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2015/02/08/2574FD8800000578-0-image-a-31_1423405632814.jpg" height="633" width="962" alt="Fine dining: Some 215 years ago, the French emperor Napoloeon used Villa La Voglina as his headquarters for the Battle of Marengo" class="blkBorder img-share"/>
</div>    <p class="imageCaption">Fine dining: Some 215 years ago, the French emperor Napoloeon used Villa La Voglina as his headquarters for the Battle of Marengo</p></div><div class="mol-img-group xwArtSplitter">    <div class="mol-img">  <img id="i-682be28e778b0d99" src="http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2015/02/08/2574FD0100000578-0-image-a-51_1423405715404.jpg" height="641" width="962" alt="One of more than a dozen bedrooms: The property also has two dining rooms, two kitchens, ten reception rooms and a guest house" class="blkBorder img-share"/>
</div>    <p class="imageCaption">One of more than a dozen bedrooms: The property also has two dining rooms, two kitchens, ten reception rooms and a guest house</p></div><p class="mol-para-with-font"><font style="font-size:1.2em">Some 215 years ago, the French emperor used Villa La Voglina as his headquarters for the Battle of Marengo.</font></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><font style="font-size:1.2em">The fighting between the French and Austrians took place near the city of Alessandria in Piemonte on June 14, 1800.</font></p><div><div class="related-carousel with-fb news half"
